3462     /* Worker function; do not call directly. */
3463     static
3464     IRAtom* expr2vbits_Load_WRK ( MCEnv* mce, 
3465                                   IREndness end, IRType ty, 
3466                                   IRAtom* addr, UInt bias )
3467     {
3468        void*    helper;
3469        Char*    hname;
3470        IRDirty* di;
3471        IRTemp   datavbits;
3472        IRAtom*  addrAct;
3473     
3474        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce,addr));
3475        tl_assert(end == Iend_LE || end == Iend_BE);
3476     
3477        /* First, emit a definedness test for the address.  This also sets
3478           the address (shadow) to 'defined' following the test. */
3479        complainIfUndefined( mce, addr );
3480     
3481        /* Now cook up a call to the relevant helper function, to read the
3482           data V bits from shadow memory. */
3483        ty = shadowTypeV(ty);
3484     
3485        if (end == Iend_LE) {   
3486           switch (ty) {
3487              case Ity_I64: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV64le);
3488                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV64le)";
3489                            break;
3490              case Ity_I32: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV32le);
3491                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV32le)";
3492                            break;
3493              case Ity_I16: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV16le);
3494                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV16le)";
3495                            break;
3496              case Ity_I8:  helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV8);
3497                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV8)";
3498                            break;
3499              default:      ppIRType(ty);
3500                            VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:do_shadow_Load(LE)");
3501           }
3502        } else {
3503           switch (ty) {
3504              case Ity_I64: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV64be);
3505                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV64be)";
3506                            break;
3507              case Ity_I32: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV32be);
3508                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV32be)";
3509                            break;
3510              case Ity_I16: helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV16be);
3511                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV16be)";
3512                            break;
3513              case Ity_I8:  helper = &MC_(helperc_LOADV8);
3514                            hname = "MC_(helperc_LOADV8)";
3515                            break;
3516              default:      ppIRType(ty);
3517                            VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:do_shadow_Load(BE)");
3518           }
3519        }
3520     
3521        /* Generate the actual address into addrAct. */
3522        if (bias == 0) {
3523           addrAct = addr;
3524        } else {
3525           IROp    mkAdd;
3526           IRAtom* eBias;
3527           IRType  tyAddr  = mce->hWordTy;
3528           tl_assert( tyAddr == Ity_I32 || tyAddr == Ity_I64 );
3529           mkAdd   = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? Iop_Add32 : Iop_Add64;
3530           eBias   = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? mkU32(bias) : mkU64(bias);
3531           addrAct = assignNew('V', mce, tyAddr, binop(mkAdd, addr, eBias) );
3532        }
3533     
3534        /* We need to have a place to park the V bits we're just about to
3535           read. */
3536        datavbits = newTemp(mce, ty, VSh);
3537        di = unsafeIRDirty_1_N( datavbits, 
3538                                1/*regparms*/, 
3539                                hname, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( helper ), 
3540                                mkIRExprVec_1( addrAct ));
3541        setHelperAnns( mce, di );
3542        stmt( 'V', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(di) );
3543     
3544        return mkexpr(datavbits);
3545     }

3547     
3548     static
3549     IRAtom* expr2vbits_Load ( MCEnv* mce, 
3550                               IREndness end, IRType ty, 
3551                               IRAtom* addr, UInt bias )
3552     {
3553        IRAtom *v64hi, *v64lo;
3554        tl_assert(end == Iend_LE || end == Iend_BE);
3555        switch (shadowTypeV(ty)) {
3556           case Ity_I8: 
3557           case Ity_I16: 
3558           case Ity_I32: 
3559           case Ity_I64:
3560              return expr2vbits_Load_WRK(mce, end, ty, addr, bias);
3561           case Ity_V128:
3562              if (end == Iend_LE) {
3563                 v64lo = expr2vbits_Load_WRK(mce, end, Ity_I64, addr, bias);
3564                 v64hi = expr2vbits_Load_WRK(mce, end, Ity_I64, addr, bias+8);
3565              } else {
3566                 v64hi = expr2vbits_Load_WRK(mce, end, Ity_I64, addr, bias);
3567                 v64lo = expr2vbits_Load_WRK(mce, end, Ity_I64, addr, bias+8);
3568              }
3569              return assignNew( 'V', mce, 
3570                                Ity_V128, 
3571                                binop(Iop_64HLtoV128, v64hi, v64lo));
3572           default:
3573              VG_(tool_panic)("expr2vbits_Load");
3574        }
3575     }

3577     
3578     static
3579     IRAtom* expr2vbits_Mux0X ( MCEnv* mce, 
3580                                IRAtom* cond, IRAtom* expr0, IRAtom* exprX )
3581     {
3582        IRAtom *vbitsC, *vbits0, *vbitsX;
3583        IRType ty;
3584        /* Given Mux0X(cond,expr0,exprX), generate
3585              Mux0X(cond,expr0#,exprX#) `UifU` PCast(cond#)
3586           That is, steer the V bits like the originals, but trash the 
3587           result if the steering value is undefined.  This gives 
3588           lazy propagation. */
3589        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cond));
3590        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, expr0));
3591        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, exprX));
3592     
3593        vbitsC = expr2vbits(mce, cond);
3594        vbits0 = expr2vbits(mce, expr0);
3595        vbitsX = expr2vbits(mce, exprX);
3596        ty = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, vbits0);
3597     
3598        return
3599           mkUifU(mce, ty, assignNew('V', mce, ty, 
3600                                          IRExpr_Mux0X(cond, vbits0, vbitsX)),
3601                           mkPCastTo(mce, ty, vbitsC) );
3602     }

3604     /* --------- This is the main expression-handling function. --------- */
3605     
3606     static
3607     IRExpr* expr2vbits ( MCEnv* mce, IRExpr* e )
3608     {
3609        switch (e->tag) {
3610     
3611           case Iex_Get:
3612              return shadow_GET( mce, e->Iex.Get.offset, e->Iex.Get.ty );
3613     
3614           case Iex_GetI:
3615              return shadow_GETI( mce, e->Iex.GetI.descr, 
3616                                       e->Iex.GetI.ix, e->Iex.GetI.bias );
3617     
3618           case Iex_RdTmp:
3619              return IRExpr_RdTmp( findShadowTmpV(mce, e->Iex.RdTmp.tmp) );
3620     
3621           case Iex_Const:
3622              return definedOfType(shadowTypeV(typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, e)));
3623     
3624           case Iex_Qop:
3625              return expr2vbits_Qop(
3626                        mce,
3627                        e->Iex.Qop.op,
3628                        e->Iex.Qop.arg1, e->Iex.Qop.arg2,
3629     		   e->Iex.Qop.arg3, e->Iex.Qop.arg4
3630                     );
3631     
3632           case Iex_Triop:
3633              return expr2vbits_Triop(
3634                        mce,
3635                        e->Iex.Triop.op,
3636                        e->Iex.Triop.arg1, e->Iex.Triop.arg2, e->Iex.Triop.arg3
3637                     );
3638     
3639           case Iex_Binop:
3640              return expr2vbits_Binop(
3641                        mce,
3642                        e->Iex.Binop.op,
3643                        e->Iex.Binop.arg1, e->Iex.Binop.arg2
3644                     );
3645     
3646           case Iex_Unop:
3647              return expr2vbits_Unop( mce, e->Iex.Unop.op, e->Iex.Unop.arg );
3648     
3649           case Iex_Load:
3650              return expr2vbits_Load( mce, e->Iex.Load.end,
3651                                           e->Iex.Load.ty, 
3652                                           e->Iex.Load.addr, 0/*addr bias*/ );
3653     
3654           case Iex_CCall:
3655              return mkLazyN( mce, e->Iex.CCall.args, 
3656                                   e->Iex.CCall.retty,
3657                                   e->Iex.CCall.cee );
3658     
3659           case Iex_Mux0X:
3660              return expr2vbits_Mux0X( mce, e->Iex.Mux0X.cond, e->Iex.Mux0X.expr0, 
3661                                            e->Iex.Mux0X.exprX);
3662     
3663           default: 
3664              VG_(printf)("\n");
3665              ppIRExpr(e);
3666              VG_(printf)("\n");
3667              VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck: expr2vbits");
3668        }
3669     }

3674     
3675     /* Widen a value to the host word size. */
3676     
3677     static
3678     IRExpr* zwidenToHostWord ( MCEnv* mce, IRAtom* vatom )
3679     {
3680        IRType ty, tyH;
3681     
3682        /* vatom is vbits-value and as such can only have a shadow type. */
3683        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce,vatom));
3684     
3685        ty  = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, vatom);
3686        tyH = mce->hWordTy;
3687     
3688        if (tyH == Ity_I32) {
3689           switch (ty) {
3690              case Ity_I32:
3691                 return vatom;
3692              case Ity_I16:
3693                 return assignNew('V', mce, tyH, unop(Iop_16Uto32, vatom));
3694              case Ity_I8:
3695                 return assignNew('V', mce, tyH, unop(Iop_8Uto32, vatom));
3696              default:
3697                 goto unhandled;
3698           }
3699        } else
3700        if (tyH == Ity_I64) {
3701           switch (ty) {
3702              case Ity_I32:
3703                 return assignNew('V', mce, tyH, unop(Iop_32Uto64, vatom));
3704              case Ity_I16:
3705                 return assignNew('V', mce, tyH, unop(Iop_32Uto64, 
3706                        assignNew('V', mce, Ity_I32, unop(Iop_16Uto32, vatom))));
3707              case Ity_I8:
3708                 return assignNew('V', mce, tyH, unop(Iop_32Uto64, 
3709                        assignNew('V', mce, Ity_I32, unop(Iop_8Uto32, vatom))));
3710              default:
3711                 goto unhandled;
3712           }
3713        } else {
3714           goto unhandled;
3715        }
3716       unhandled:
3717        VG_(printf)("\nty = "); ppIRType(ty); VG_(printf)("\n");
3718        VG_(tool_panic)("zwidenToHostWord");
3719     }
3720     
3721     
3722     /* Generate a shadow store.  addr is always the original address atom.
3723        You can pass in either originals or V-bits for the data atom, but
3724        obviously not both.  guard :: Ity_I1 controls whether the store
3725        really happens; NULL means it unconditionally does.  Note that
3726        guard itself is not checked for definedness; the caller of this
3727        function must do that if necessary. */
3728     
3729     static 
3730     void do_shadow_Store ( MCEnv* mce, 
3731                            IREndness end,
3732                            IRAtom* addr, UInt bias,
3733                            IRAtom* data, IRAtom* vdata,
3734                            IRAtom* guard )
3735     {
3736        IROp     mkAdd;
3737        IRType   ty, tyAddr;
3738        void*    helper = NULL;
3739        Char*    hname = NULL;
3740        IRConst* c;
3741     
3742        tyAddr = mce->hWordTy;
3743        mkAdd  = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? Iop_Add32 : Iop_Add64;
3744        tl_assert( tyAddr == Ity_I32 || tyAddr == Ity_I64 );
3745        tl_assert( end == Iend_LE || end == Iend_BE );
3746     
3747        if (data) {
3748           tl_assert(!vdata);
3749           tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, data));
3750           tl_assert(bias == 0);
3751           vdata = expr2vbits( mce, data );
3752        } else {
3753           tl_assert(vdata);
3754        }
3755     
3756        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce,addr));
3757        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce,vdata));
3758     
3759        if (guard) {
3760           tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, guard));
3761           tl_assert(typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, guard) == Ity_I1);
3762        }
3763     
3764        ty = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, vdata);
3765     
3766        // If we're not doing undefined value checking, pretend that this value
3767        // is "all valid".  That lets Vex's optimiser remove some of the V bit
3768        // shadow computation ops that precede it.
3769        if (MC_(clo_mc_level) == 1) {
3770           switch (ty) {
3771              case Ity_V128: // V128 weirdness
3772                             c = IRConst_V128(V_BITS16_DEFINED); break;
3773              case Ity_I64:  c = IRConst_U64 (V_BITS64_DEFINED); break;
3774              case Ity_I32:  c = IRConst_U32 (V_BITS32_DEFINED); break;
3775              case Ity_I16:  c = IRConst_U16 (V_BITS16_DEFINED); break;
3776              case Ity_I8:   c = IRConst_U8  (V_BITS8_DEFINED);  break;
3777              default:       VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:do_shadow_Store(LE)");
3778           }
3779           vdata = IRExpr_Const( c );
3780        }
3781     
3782        /* First, emit a definedness test for the address.  This also sets
3783           the address (shadow) to 'defined' following the test. */
3784        complainIfUndefined( mce, addr );
3785     
3786        /* Now decide which helper function to call to write the data V
3787           bits into shadow memory. */
3788        if (end == Iend_LE) {
3789           switch (ty) {
3790              case Ity_V128: /* we'll use the helper twice */
3791              case Ity_I64: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV64le);
3792                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV64le)";
3793                            break;
3794              case Ity_I32: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV32le);
3795                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV32le)";
3796                            break;
3797              case Ity_I16: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV16le);
3798                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV16le)";
3799                            break;
3800              case Ity_I8:  helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV8);
3801                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV8)";
3802                            break;
3803              default:      VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:do_shadow_Store(LE)");
3804           }
3805        } else {
3806           switch (ty) {
3807              case Ity_V128: /* we'll use the helper twice */
3808              case Ity_I64: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV64be);
3809                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV64be)";
3810                            break;
3811              case Ity_I32: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV32be);
3812                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV32be)";
3813                            break;
3814              case Ity_I16: helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV16be);
3815                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV16be)";
3816                            break;
3817              case Ity_I8:  helper = &MC_(helperc_STOREV8);
3818                            hname = "MC_(helperc_STOREV8)";
3819                            break;
3820              default:      VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:do_shadow_Store(BE)");
3821           }
3822        }
3823     
3824        if (ty == Ity_V128) {
3825     
3826           /* V128-bit case */
3827           /* See comment in next clause re 64-bit regparms */
3828           /* also, need to be careful about endianness */
3829     
3830           Int     offLo64, offHi64;
3831           IRDirty *diLo64, *diHi64;
3832           IRAtom  *addrLo64, *addrHi64;
3833           IRAtom  *vdataLo64, *vdataHi64;
3834           IRAtom  *eBiasLo64, *eBiasHi64;
3835     
3836           if (end == Iend_LE) {
3837              offLo64 = 0;
3838              offHi64 = 8;
3839           } else {
3840              offLo64 = 8;
3841              offHi64 = 0;
3842           }
3843     
3844           eBiasLo64 = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? mkU32(bias+offLo64) : mkU64(bias+offLo64);
3845           addrLo64  = assignNew('V', mce, tyAddr, binop(mkAdd, addr, eBiasLo64) );
3846           vdataLo64 = assignNew('V', mce, Ity_I64, unop(Iop_V128to64, vdata));
3847           diLo64    = unsafeIRDirty_0_N( 
3848                          1/*regparms*/, 
3849                          hname, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( helper ), 
3850                          mkIRExprVec_2( addrLo64, vdataLo64 )
3851                       );
3852           eBiasHi64 = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? mkU32(bias+offHi64) : mkU64(bias+offHi64);
3853           addrHi64  = assignNew('V', mce, tyAddr, binop(mkAdd, addr, eBiasHi64) );
3854           vdataHi64 = assignNew('V', mce, Ity_I64, unop(Iop_V128HIto64, vdata));
3855           diHi64    = unsafeIRDirty_0_N( 
3856                          1/*regparms*/, 
3857                          hname, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( helper ), 
3858                          mkIRExprVec_2( addrHi64, vdataHi64 )
3859                       );
3860           if (guard) diLo64->guard = guard;
3861           if (guard) diHi64->guard = guard;
3862           setHelperAnns( mce, diLo64 );
3863           setHelperAnns( mce, diHi64 );
3864           stmt( 'V', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(diLo64) );
3865           stmt( 'V', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(diHi64) );
3866     
3867        } else {
3868     
3869           IRDirty *di;
3870           IRAtom  *addrAct;
3871     
3872           /* 8/16/32/64-bit cases */
3873           /* Generate the actual address into addrAct. */
3874           if (bias == 0) {
3875              addrAct = addr;
3876           } else {
3877              IRAtom* eBias   = tyAddr==Ity_I32 ? mkU32(bias) : mkU64(bias);
3878              addrAct = assignNew('V', mce, tyAddr, binop(mkAdd, addr, eBias));
3879           }
3880     
3881           if (ty == Ity_I64) {
3882              /* We can't do this with regparm 2 on 32-bit platforms, since
3883                 the back ends aren't clever enough to handle 64-bit
3884                 regparm args.  Therefore be different. */
3885              di = unsafeIRDirty_0_N( 
3886                      1/*regparms*/, 
3887                      hname, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( helper ), 
3888                      mkIRExprVec_2( addrAct, vdata )
3889                   );
3890           } else {
3891              di = unsafeIRDirty_0_N( 
3892                      2/*regparms*/, 
3893                      hname, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( helper ), 
3894                      mkIRExprVec_2( addrAct,
3895                                     zwidenToHostWord( mce, vdata ))
3896                   );
3897           }
3898           if (guard) di->guard = guard;
3899           setHelperAnns( mce, di );
3900           stmt( 'V', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(di) );
3901        }
3902     
3903     }

3905     
3906     /* Do lazy pessimistic propagation through a dirty helper call, by
3907        looking at the annotations on it.  This is the most complex part of
3908        Memcheck. */
3909     
3910     static IRType szToITy ( Int n )
3911     {
3912        switch (n) {
3913           case 1: return Ity_I8;
3914           case 2: return Ity_I16;
3915           case 4: return Ity_I32;
3916           case 8: return Ity_I64;
3917           default: VG_(tool_panic)("szToITy(memcheck)");
3918        }
3919     }
3920     
3921     static
3922     void do_shadow_Dirty ( MCEnv* mce, IRDirty* d )
3923     {
3924        Int       i, n, toDo, gSz, gOff;
3925        IRAtom    *src, *here, *curr;
3926        IRType    tySrc, tyDst;
3927        IRTemp    dst;
3928        IREndness end;
3929     
3930        /* What's the native endianness?  We need to know this. */
3931     #  if defined(VG_BIGENDIAN)
3932        end = Iend_BE;
3933     #  elif defined(VG_LITTLEENDIAN)
3934        end = Iend_LE;
3935     #  else
3936     #    error "Unknown endianness"
3937     #  endif
3938     
3939        /* First check the guard. */
3940        complainIfUndefined(mce, d->guard);
3941     
3942        /* Now round up all inputs and PCast over them. */
3943        curr = definedOfType(Ity_I32);
3944     
3945        /* Inputs: unmasked args */
3946        for (i = 0; d->args[i]; i++) {
3947           if (d->cee->mcx_mask & (1<<i)) {
3948              /* ignore this arg */
3949           } else {
3950              here = mkPCastTo( mce, Ity_I32, expr2vbits(mce, d->args[i]) );
3951              curr = mkUifU32(mce, here, curr);
3952           }
3953        }
3954     
3955        /* Inputs: guest state that we read. */
3956        for (i = 0; i < d->nFxState; i++) {
3957           tl_assert(d->fxState[i].fx != Ifx_None);
3958           if (d->fxState[i].fx == Ifx_Write)
3959              continue;
3960     
3961           /* Ignore any sections marked as 'always defined'. */
3962           if (isAlwaysDefd(mce, d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size )) {
3963              if (0)
3964              VG_(printf)("memcheck: Dirty gst: ignored off %d, sz %d\n",
3965                          d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size );
3966              continue;
3967           }
3968     
3969           /* This state element is read or modified.  So we need to
3970              consider it.  If larger than 8 bytes, deal with it in 8-byte
3971              chunks. */
3972           gSz  = d->fxState[i].size;
3973           gOff = d->fxState[i].offset;
3974           tl_assert(gSz > 0);
3975           while (True) {
3976              if (gSz == 0) break;
3977              n = gSz <= 8 ? gSz : 8;
3978              /* update 'curr' with UifU of the state slice 
3979                 gOff .. gOff+n-1 */
3980              tySrc = szToITy( n );
3981              src   = assignNew( 'V', mce, tySrc, 
3982                                      shadow_GET(mce, gOff, tySrc ) );
3983              here = mkPCastTo( mce, Ity_I32, src );
3984              curr = mkUifU32(mce, here, curr);
3985              gSz -= n;
3986              gOff += n;
3987           }
3988     
3989        }
3990     
3991        /* Inputs: memory.  First set up some info needed regardless of
3992           whether we're doing reads or writes. */
3993     
3994        if (d->mFx != Ifx_None) {
3995           /* Because we may do multiple shadow loads/stores from the same
3996              base address, it's best to do a single test of its
3997              definedness right now.  Post-instrumentation optimisation
3998              should remove all but this test. */
3999           IRType tyAddr;
4000           tl_assert(d->mAddr);
4001           complainIfUndefined(mce, d->mAddr);
4002     
4003           tyAddr = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, d->mAddr);
4004           tl_assert(tyAddr == Ity_I32 || tyAddr == Ity_I64);
4005           tl_assert(tyAddr == mce->hWordTy); /* not really right */
4006        }
4007     
4008        /* Deal with memory inputs (reads or modifies) */
4009        if (d->mFx == Ifx_Read || d->mFx == Ifx_Modify) {
4010           toDo   = d->mSize;
4011           /* chew off 32-bit chunks.  We don't care about the endianness
4012              since it's all going to be condensed down to a single bit,
4013              but nevertheless choose an endianness which is hopefully
4014              native to the platform. */
4015           while (toDo >= 4) {
4016              here = mkPCastTo( 
4017                        mce, Ity_I32,
4018                        expr2vbits_Load ( mce, end, Ity_I32, 
4019                                          d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo )
4020                     );
4021              curr = mkUifU32(mce, here, curr);
4022              toDo -= 4;
4023           }
4024           /* chew off 16-bit chunks */
4025           while (toDo >= 2) {
4026              here = mkPCastTo( 
4027                        mce, Ity_I32,
4028                        expr2vbits_Load ( mce, end, Ity_I16, 
4029                                          d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo )
4030                     );
4031              curr = mkUifU32(mce, here, curr);
4032              toDo -= 2;
4033           }
4034           tl_assert(toDo == 0); /* also need to handle 1-byte excess */
4035        }
4036     
4037        /* Whew!  So curr is a 32-bit V-value summarising pessimistically
4038           all the inputs to the helper.  Now we need to re-distribute the
4039           results to all destinations. */
4040     
4041        /* Outputs: the destination temporary, if there is one. */
4042        if (d->tmp != IRTemp_INVALID) {
4043           dst   = findShadowTmpV(mce, d->tmp);
4044           tyDst = typeOfIRTemp(mce->sb->tyenv, d->tmp);
4045           assign( 'V', mce, dst, mkPCastTo( mce, tyDst, curr) );
4046        }
4047     
4048        /* Outputs: guest state that we write or modify. */
4049        for (i = 0; i < d->nFxState; i++) {
4050           tl_assert(d->fxState[i].fx != Ifx_None);
4051           if (d->fxState[i].fx == Ifx_Read)
4052              continue;
4053           /* Ignore any sections marked as 'always defined'. */
4054           if (isAlwaysDefd(mce, d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size ))
4055              continue;
4056           /* This state element is written or modified.  So we need to
4057              consider it.  If larger than 8 bytes, deal with it in 8-byte
4058              chunks. */
4059           gSz  = d->fxState[i].size;
4060           gOff = d->fxState[i].offset;
4061           tl_assert(gSz > 0);
4062           while (True) {
4063              if (gSz == 0) break;
4064              n = gSz <= 8 ? gSz : 8;
4065              /* Write suitably-casted 'curr' to the state slice 
4066                 gOff .. gOff+n-1 */
4067              tyDst = szToITy( n );
4068              do_shadow_PUT( mce, gOff,
4069                                  NULL, /* original atom */
4070                                  mkPCastTo( mce, tyDst, curr ) );
4071              gSz -= n;
4072              gOff += n;
4073           }
4074        }
4075     
4076        /* Outputs: memory that we write or modify.  Same comments about
4077           endianness as above apply. */
4078        if (d->mFx == Ifx_Write || d->mFx == Ifx_Modify) {
4079           toDo   = d->mSize;
4080           /* chew off 32-bit chunks */
4081           while (toDo >= 4) {
4082              do_shadow_Store( mce, end, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo,
4083                               NULL, /* original data */
4084                               mkPCastTo( mce, Ity_I32, curr ),
4085                               NULL/*guard*/ );
4086              toDo -= 4;
4087           }
4088           /* chew off 16-bit chunks */
4089           while (toDo >= 2) {
4090              do_shadow_Store( mce, end, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo,
4091                               NULL, /* original data */
4092                               mkPCastTo( mce, Ity_I16, curr ),
4093                               NULL/*guard*/ );
4094              toDo -= 2;
4095           }
4096           tl_assert(toDo == 0); /* also need to handle 1-byte excess */
4097        }
4098     
4099     }

4101     
4102     /* We have an ABI hint telling us that [base .. base+len-1] is to
4103        become undefined ("writable").  Generate code to call a helper to
4104        notify the A/V bit machinery of this fact.
4105     
4106        We call 
4107        void MC_(helperc_MAKE_STACK_UNINIT) ( Addr base, UWord len,
4108                                                         Addr nia );
4109     */
4110     static
4111     void do_AbiHint ( MCEnv* mce, IRExpr* base, Int len, IRExpr* nia )
4112     {
4113        IRDirty* di;
4114        /* Minor optimisation: if not doing origin tracking, ignore the
4115           supplied nia and pass zero instead.  This is on the basis that
4116           MC_(helperc_MAKE_STACK_UNINIT) will ignore it anyway, and we can
4117           almost always generate a shorter instruction to put zero into a
4118           register than any other value. */
4119        if (MC_(clo_mc_level) < 3)
4120           nia = mkIRExpr_HWord(0);
4121     
4122        di = unsafeIRDirty_0_N(
4123                0/*regparms*/,
4124                "MC_(helperc_MAKE_STACK_UNINIT)",
4125                VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( &MC_(helperc_MAKE_STACK_UNINIT) ),
4126                mkIRExprVec_3( base, mkIRExpr_HWord( (UInt)len), nia )
4127             );
4128        stmt( 'V', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(di) );
4129     }

4132     /* ------ Dealing with IRCAS (big and complex) ------ */
4133     
4134     /* FWDS */
4135     static IRAtom* gen_load_b  ( MCEnv* mce, Int szB, 
4136                                  IRAtom* baseaddr, Int offset );
4137     static IRAtom* gen_maxU32  ( MCEnv* mce, IRAtom* b1, IRAtom* b2 );
4138     static void    gen_store_b ( MCEnv* mce, Int szB,
4139                                  IRAtom* baseaddr, Int offset, IRAtom* dataB,
4140                                  IRAtom* guard );
4141     
4142     static void do_shadow_CAS_single ( MCEnv* mce, IRCAS* cas );
4143     static void do_shadow_CAS_double ( MCEnv* mce, IRCAS* cas );
4144     
4145     
4146     /* Either ORIG and SHADOW are both IRExpr.RdTmps, or they are both
4147        IRExpr.Consts, else this asserts.  If they are both Consts, it
4148        doesn't do anything.  So that just leaves the RdTmp case.
4149     
4150        In which case: this assigns the shadow value SHADOW to the IR
4151        shadow temporary associated with ORIG.  That is, ORIG, being an
4152        original temporary, will have a shadow temporary associated with
4153        it.  However, in the case envisaged here, there will so far have
4154        been no IR emitted to actually write a shadow value into that
4155        temporary.  What this routine does is to (emit IR to) copy the
4156        value in SHADOW into said temporary, so that after this call,
4157        IRExpr.RdTmps of ORIG's shadow temp will correctly pick up the
4158        value in SHADOW.
4159     
4160        Point is to allow callers to compute "by hand" a shadow value for
4161        ORIG, and force it to be associated with ORIG.
4162     
4163        How do we know that that shadow associated with ORIG has not so far
4164        been assigned to?  Well, we don't per se know that, but supposing
4165        it had.  Then this routine would create a second assignment to it,
4166        and later the IR sanity checker would barf.  But that never
4167        happens.  QED.
4168     */
4169     static void bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig ( UChar how,
4170                                           MCEnv* mce,
4171                                           IRAtom* orig, IRAtom* shadow )
4172     {
4173        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, orig));
4174        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, shadow));
4175        switch (orig->tag) {
4176           case Iex_Const:
4177              tl_assert(shadow->tag == Iex_Const);
4178              break;
4179           case Iex_RdTmp:
4180              tl_assert(shadow->tag == Iex_RdTmp);
4181              if (how == 'V') {
4182                 assign('V', mce, findShadowTmpV(mce,orig->Iex.RdTmp.tmp),
4183                        shadow);
4184              } else {
4185                 tl_assert(how == 'B');
4186                 assign('B', mce, findShadowTmpB(mce,orig->Iex.RdTmp.tmp),
4187                        shadow);
4188              }
4189              break;
4190           default:
4191              tl_assert(0);
4192        }
4193     }
4194     
4195     
4196     static
4197     void do_shadow_CAS ( MCEnv* mce, IRCAS* cas )
4198     {
4199        /* Scheme is (both single- and double- cases):
4200     
4201           1. fetch data#,dataB (the proposed new value)
4202     
4203           2. fetch expd#,expdB (what we expect to see at the address)
4204     
4205           3. check definedness of address
4206     
4207           4. load old#,oldB from shadow memory; this also checks
4208              addressibility of the address
4209     
4210           5. the CAS itself
4211     
4212           6. compute "expected == old".  See COMMENT_ON_CasCmpEQ below.
4213     
4214           7. if "expected == old" (as computed by (6))
4215                 store data#,dataB to shadow memory
4216     
4217           Note that 5 reads 'old' but 4 reads 'old#'.  Similarly, 5 stores
4218           'data' but 7 stores 'data#'.  Hence it is possible for the
4219           shadow data to be incorrectly checked and/or updated:
4220     
4221           * 7 is at least gated correctly, since the 'expected == old'
4222             condition is derived from outputs of 5.  However, the shadow
4223             write could happen too late: imagine after 5 we are
4224             descheduled, a different thread runs, writes a different
4225             (shadow) value at the address, and then we resume, hence
4226             overwriting the shadow value written by the other thread.
4227     
4228           Because the original memory access is atomic, there's no way to
4229           make both the original and shadow accesses into a single atomic
4230           thing, hence this is unavoidable.
4231     
4232           At least as Valgrind stands, I don't think it's a problem, since
4233           we're single threaded *and* we guarantee that there are no
4234           context switches during the execution of any specific superblock
4235           -- context switches can only happen at superblock boundaries.
4236     
4237           If Valgrind ever becomes MT in the future, then it might be more
4238           of a problem.  A possible kludge would be to artificially
4239           associate with the location, a lock, which we must acquire and
4240           release around the transaction as a whole.  Hmm, that probably
4241           would't work properly since it only guards us against other
4242           threads doing CASs on the same location, not against other
4243           threads doing normal reads and writes.
4244     
4245           ------------------------------------------------------------
4246     
4247           COMMENT_ON_CasCmpEQ:
4248     
4249           Note two things.  Firstly, in the sequence above, we compute
4250           "expected == old", but we don't check definedness of it.  Why
4251           not?  Also, the x86 and amd64 front ends use
4252           Iop_CmpCas{EQ,NE}{8,16,32,64} comparisons to make the equivalent
4253           determination (expected == old ?) for themselves, and we also
4254           don't check definedness for those primops; we just say that the
4255           result is defined.  Why?  Details follow.
4256     
4257           x86/amd64 contains various forms of locked insns:
4258           * lock prefix before all basic arithmetic insn; 
4259             eg lock xorl %reg1,(%reg2)
4260           * atomic exchange reg-mem
4261           * compare-and-swaps
4262     
4263           Rather than attempt to represent them all, which would be a
4264           royal PITA, I used a result from Maurice Herlihy
4265           (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maurice_Herlihy), in which he
4266           demonstrates that compare-and-swap is a primitive more general
4267           than the other two, and so can be used to represent all of them.
4268           So the translation scheme for (eg) lock incl (%reg) is as
4269           follows:
4270     
4271             again:
4272              old = * %reg
4273              new = old + 1
4274              atomically { if (* %reg == old) { * %reg = new } else { goto again } }
4275     
4276           The "atomically" is the CAS bit.  The scheme is always the same:
4277           get old value from memory, compute new value, atomically stuff
4278           new value back in memory iff the old value has not changed (iow,
4279           no other thread modified it in the meantime).  If it has changed
4280           then we've been out-raced and we have to start over.
4281     
4282           Now that's all very neat, but it has the bad side effect of
4283           introducing an explicit equality test into the translation.
4284           Consider the behaviour of said code on a memory location which
4285           is uninitialised.  We will wind up doing a comparison on
4286           uninitialised data, and mc duly complains.
4287     
4288           What's difficult about this is, the common case is that the
4289           location is uncontended, and so we're usually comparing the same
4290           value (* %reg) with itself.  So we shouldn't complain even if it
4291           is undefined.  But mc doesn't know that.
4292     
4293           My solution is to mark the == in the IR specially, so as to tell
4294           mc that it almost certainly compares a value with itself, and we
4295           should just regard the result as always defined.  Rather than
4296           add a bit to all IROps, I just cloned Iop_CmpEQ{8,16,32,64} into
4297           Iop_CasCmpEQ{8,16,32,64} so as not to disturb anything else.
4298     
4299           So there's always the question of, can this give a false
4300           negative?  eg, imagine that initially, * %reg is defined; and we
4301           read that; but then in the gap between the read and the CAS, a
4302           different thread writes an undefined (and different) value at
4303           the location.  Then the CAS in this thread will fail and we will
4304           go back to "again:", but without knowing that the trip back
4305           there was based on an undefined comparison.  No matter; at least
4306           the other thread won the race and the location is correctly
4307           marked as undefined.  What if it wrote an uninitialised version
4308           of the same value that was there originally, though?
4309     
4310           etc etc.  Seems like there's a small corner case in which we
4311           might lose the fact that something's defined -- we're out-raced
4312           in between the "old = * reg" and the "atomically {", _and_ the
4313           other thread is writing in an undefined version of what's
4314           already there.  Well, that seems pretty unlikely.
4315     
4316           ---
4317     
4318           If we ever need to reinstate it .. code which generates a
4319           definedness test for "expected == old" was removed at r10432 of
4320           this file.
4321        */
4322        if (cas->oldHi == IRTemp_INVALID) {
4323           do_shadow_CAS_single( mce, cas );
4324        } else {
4325           do_shadow_CAS_double( mce, cas );
4326        }
4327     }
4328     
4329     
4330     static void do_shadow_CAS_single ( MCEnv* mce, IRCAS* cas )
4331     {
4332        IRAtom *vdataLo = NULL, *bdataLo = NULL;
4333        IRAtom *vexpdLo = NULL, *bexpdLo = NULL;
4334        IRAtom *voldLo  = NULL, *boldLo  = NULL;
4335        IRAtom *expd_eq_old = NULL;
4336        IROp   opCasCmpEQ;
4337        Int    elemSzB;
4338        IRType elemTy;
4339        Bool   otrak = MC_(clo_mc_level) >= 3; /* a shorthand */
4340     
4341        /* single CAS */
4342        tl_assert(cas->oldHi == IRTemp_INVALID);
4343        tl_assert(cas->expdHi == NULL);
4344        tl_assert(cas->dataHi == NULL);
4345     
4346        elemTy = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, cas->expdLo);
4347        switch (elemTy) {
4348           case Ity_I8:  elemSzB = 1; opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ8;  break;
4349           case Ity_I16: elemSzB = 2; opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ16; break;
4350           case Ity_I32: elemSzB = 4; opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ32; break;
4351           case Ity_I64: elemSzB = 8; opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ64; break;
4352           default: tl_assert(0); /* IR defn disallows any other types */
4353        }
4354     
4355        /* 1. fetch data# (the proposed new value) */
4356        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->dataLo));
4357        vdataLo
4358           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->dataLo));
4359        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vdataLo));
4360        if (otrak) {
4361           bdataLo
4362              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->dataLo));
4363           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bdataLo));
4364        }
4365     
4366        /* 2. fetch expected# (what we expect to see at the address) */
4367        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->expdLo));
4368        vexpdLo
4369           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->expdLo));
4370        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vexpdLo));
4371        if (otrak) {
4372           bexpdLo
4373              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->expdLo));
4374           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bexpdLo));
4375        }
4376     
4377        /* 3. check definedness of address */
4378        /* 4. fetch old# from shadow memory; this also checks
4379              addressibility of the address */
4380        voldLo
4381           = assignNew(
4382                'V', mce, elemTy,
4383                expr2vbits_Load( 
4384                   mce,
4385                   cas->end, elemTy, cas->addr, 0/*Addr bias*/
4386             ));
4387        bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('V', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldLo), voldLo);
4388        if (otrak) {
4389           boldLo
4390              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32,
4391                          gen_load_b(mce, elemSzB, cas->addr, 0/*addr bias*/));
4392           bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('B', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldLo), boldLo);
4393        }
4394     
4395        /* 5. the CAS itself */
4396        stmt( 'C', mce, IRStmt_CAS(cas) );
4397     
4398        /* 6. compute "expected == old" */
4399        /* See COMMENT_ON_CasCmpEQ in this file background/rationale. */
4400        /* Note that 'C' is kinda faking it; it is indeed a non-shadow
4401           tree, but it's not copied from the input block. */
4402        expd_eq_old
4403           = assignNew('C', mce, Ity_I1,
4404                       binop(opCasCmpEQ, cas->expdLo, mkexpr(cas->oldLo)));
4405     
4406        /* 7. if "expected == old"
4407                 store data# to shadow memory */
4408        do_shadow_Store( mce, cas->end, cas->addr, 0/*bias*/,
4409                         NULL/*data*/, vdataLo/*vdata*/,
4410                         expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4411        if (otrak) {
4412           gen_store_b( mce, elemSzB, cas->addr, 0/*offset*/,
4413                        bdataLo/*bdata*/,
4414                        expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4415        }
4416     }
4417     
4418     
4419     static void do_shadow_CAS_double ( MCEnv* mce, IRCAS* cas )
4420     {
4421        IRAtom *vdataHi = NULL, *bdataHi = NULL;
4422        IRAtom *vdataLo = NULL, *bdataLo = NULL;
4423        IRAtom *vexpdHi = NULL, *bexpdHi = NULL;
4424        IRAtom *vexpdLo = NULL, *bexpdLo = NULL;
4425        IRAtom *voldHi  = NULL, *boldHi  = NULL;
4426        IRAtom *voldLo  = NULL, *boldLo  = NULL;
4427        IRAtom *xHi = NULL, *xLo = NULL, *xHL = NULL;
4428        IRAtom *expd_eq_old = NULL, *zero = NULL;
4429        IROp   opCasCmpEQ, opOr, opXor;
4430        Int    elemSzB, memOffsLo, memOffsHi;
4431        IRType elemTy;
4432        Bool   otrak = MC_(clo_mc_level) >= 3; /* a shorthand */
4433     
4434        /* double CAS */
4435        tl_assert(cas->oldHi != IRTemp_INVALID);
4436        tl_assert(cas->expdHi != NULL);
4437        tl_assert(cas->dataHi != NULL);
4438     
4439        elemTy = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, cas->expdLo);
4440        switch (elemTy) {
4441           case Ity_I8:
4442              opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ8; opOr = Iop_Or8; opXor = Iop_Xor8; 
4443              elemSzB = 1; zero = mkU8(0);
4444              break;
4445           case Ity_I16:
4446              opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ16; opOr = Iop_Or16; opXor = Iop_Xor16;
4447              elemSzB = 2; zero = mkU16(0);
4448              break;
4449           case Ity_I32:
4450              opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ32; opOr = Iop_Or32; opXor = Iop_Xor32;
4451              elemSzB = 4; zero = mkU32(0);
4452              break;
4453           case Ity_I64:
4454              opCasCmpEQ = Iop_CasCmpEQ64; opOr = Iop_Or64; opXor = Iop_Xor64;
4455              elemSzB = 8; zero = mkU64(0);
4456              break;
4457           default:
4458              tl_assert(0); /* IR defn disallows any other types */
4459        }
4460     
4461        /* 1. fetch data# (the proposed new value) */
4462        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->dataHi));
4463        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->dataLo));
4464        vdataHi
4465           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->dataHi));
4466        vdataLo
4467           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->dataLo));
4468        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vdataHi));
4469        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vdataLo));
4470        if (otrak) {
4471           bdataHi
4472              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->dataHi));
4473           bdataLo
4474              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->dataLo));
4475           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bdataHi));
4476           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bdataLo));
4477        }
4478     
4479        /* 2. fetch expected# (what we expect to see at the address) */
4480        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->expdHi));
4481        tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, cas->expdLo));
4482        vexpdHi
4483           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->expdHi));
4484        vexpdLo
4485           = assignNew('V', mce, elemTy, expr2vbits(mce, cas->expdLo));
4486        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vexpdHi));
4487        tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, vexpdLo));
4488        if (otrak) {
4489           bexpdHi
4490              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->expdHi));
4491           bexpdLo
4492              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32, schemeE(mce, cas->expdLo));
4493           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bexpdHi));
4494           tl_assert(isShadowAtom(mce, bexpdLo));
4495        }
4496     
4497        /* 3. check definedness of address */
4498        /* 4. fetch old# from shadow memory; this also checks
4499              addressibility of the address */
4500        if (cas->end == Iend_LE) {
4501           memOffsLo = 0;
4502           memOffsHi = elemSzB;
4503        } else {
4504           tl_assert(cas->end == Iend_BE);
4505           memOffsLo = elemSzB;
4506           memOffsHi = 0;
4507        }
4508        voldHi
4509           = assignNew(
4510                'V', mce, elemTy,
4511                expr2vbits_Load( 
4512                   mce,
4513                   cas->end, elemTy, cas->addr, memOffsHi/*Addr bias*/
4514             ));
4515        voldLo
4516           = assignNew(
4517                'V', mce, elemTy,
4518                expr2vbits_Load( 
4519                   mce,
4520                   cas->end, elemTy, cas->addr, memOffsLo/*Addr bias*/
4521             ));
4522        bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('V', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldHi), voldHi);
4523        bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('V', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldLo), voldLo);
4524        if (otrak) {
4525           boldHi
4526              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32,
4527                          gen_load_b(mce, elemSzB, cas->addr,
4528                                     memOffsHi/*addr bias*/));
4529           boldLo
4530              = assignNew('B', mce, Ity_I32,
4531                          gen_load_b(mce, elemSzB, cas->addr,
4532                                     memOffsLo/*addr bias*/));
4533           bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('B', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldHi), boldHi);
4534           bind_shadow_tmp_to_orig('B', mce, mkexpr(cas->oldLo), boldLo);
4535        }
4536     
4537        /* 5. the CAS itself */
4538        stmt( 'C', mce, IRStmt_CAS(cas) );
4539     
4540        /* 6. compute "expected == old" */
4541        /* See COMMENT_ON_CasCmpEQ in this file background/rationale. */
4542        /* Note that 'C' is kinda faking it; it is indeed a non-shadow
4543           tree, but it's not copied from the input block. */
4544        /*
4545           xHi = oldHi ^ expdHi;
4546           xLo = oldLo ^ expdLo;
4547           xHL = xHi | xLo;
4548           expd_eq_old = xHL == 0;
4549        */
4550        xHi = assignNew('C', mce, elemTy,
4551                        binop(opXor, cas->expdHi, mkexpr(cas->oldHi))); 
4552        xLo = assignNew('C', mce, elemTy,
4553                        binop(opXor, cas->expdLo, mkexpr(cas->oldLo)));
4554        xHL = assignNew('C', mce, elemTy,
4555                        binop(opOr, xHi, xLo));
4556        expd_eq_old
4557           = assignNew('C', mce, Ity_I1,
4558                       binop(opCasCmpEQ, xHL, zero));
4559     
4560        /* 7. if "expected == old"
4561                 store data# to shadow memory */
4562        do_shadow_Store( mce, cas->end, cas->addr, memOffsHi/*bias*/,
4563                         NULL/*data*/, vdataHi/*vdata*/,
4564                         expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4565        do_shadow_Store( mce, cas->end, cas->addr, memOffsLo/*bias*/,
4566                         NULL/*data*/, vdataLo/*vdata*/,
4567                         expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4568        if (otrak) {
4569           gen_store_b( mce, elemSzB, cas->addr, memOffsHi/*offset*/,
4570                        bdataHi/*bdata*/,
4571                        expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4572           gen_store_b( mce, elemSzB, cas->addr, memOffsLo/*offset*/,
4573                        bdataLo/*bdata*/,
4574                        expd_eq_old/*guard for store*/ );
4575        }
4576     }

4578     
4579     /* ------ Dealing with LL/SC (not difficult) ------ */
4580     
4581     static void do_shadow_LLSC ( MCEnv*    mce,
4582                                  IREndness stEnd,
4583                                  IRTemp    stResult,
4584                                  IRExpr*   stAddr,
4585                                  IRExpr*   stStoredata )
4586     {
4587        /* In short: treat a load-linked like a normal load followed by an
4588           assignment of the loaded (shadow) data to the result temporary.
4589           Treat a store-conditional like a normal store, and mark the
4590           result temporary as defined. */
4591        IRType resTy  = typeOfIRTemp(mce->sb->tyenv, stResult);
4592        IRTemp resTmp = findShadowTmpV(mce, stResult);
4593     
4594        tl_assert(isIRAtom(stAddr));
4595        if (stStoredata)
4596           tl_assert(isIRAtom(stStoredata));
4597     
4598        if (stStoredata == NULL) {
4599           /* Load Linked */
4600           /* Just treat this as a normal load, followed by an assignment of
4601              the value to .result. */
4602           /* Stay sane */
4603           tl_assert(resTy == Ity_I64 || resTy == Ity_I32
4604                     || resTy == Ity_I16 || resTy == Ity_I8);
4605           assign( 'V', mce, resTmp,
4606                        expr2vbits_Load(
4607                           mce, stEnd, resTy, stAddr, 0/*addr bias*/));
4608        } else {
4609           /* Store Conditional */
4610           /* Stay sane */
4611           IRType dataTy = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv,
4612                                        stStoredata);
4613           tl_assert(dataTy == Ity_I64 || dataTy == Ity_I32
4614                     || dataTy == Ity_I16 || dataTy == Ity_I8);
4615           do_shadow_Store( mce, stEnd,
4616                                 stAddr, 0/* addr bias */,
4617                                 stStoredata,
4618                                 NULL /* shadow data */,
4619                                 NULL/*guard*/ );
4620           /* This is a store conditional, so it writes to .result a value
4621              indicating whether or not the store succeeded.  Just claim
4622              this value is always defined.  In the PowerPC interpretation
4623              of store-conditional, definedness of the success indication
4624              depends on whether the address of the store matches the
4625              reservation address.  But we can't tell that here (and
4626              anyway, we're not being PowerPC-specific).  At least we are
4627              guaranteed that the definedness of the store address, and its
4628              addressibility, will be checked as per normal.  So it seems
4629              pretty safe to just say that the success indication is always
4630              defined.
4631     
4632              In schemeS, for origin tracking, we must correspondingly set
4633              a no-origin value for the origin shadow of .result.
4634           */
4635           tl_assert(resTy == Ity_I1);
4636           assign( 'V', mce, resTmp, definedOfType(resTy) );
4637        }
4638     }

4645     static void schemeS ( MCEnv* mce, IRStmt* st );
4646     
4647     static Bool isBogusAtom ( IRAtom* at )
4648     {
4649        ULong n = 0;
4650        IRConst* con;
4651        tl_assert(isIRAtom(at));
4652        if (at->tag == Iex_RdTmp)
4653           return False;
4654        tl_assert(at->tag == Iex_Const);
4655        con = at->Iex.Const.con;
4656        switch (con->tag) {
4657           case Ico_U1:   return False;
4658           case Ico_U8:   n = (ULong)con->Ico.U8; break;
4659           case Ico_U16:  n = (ULong)con->Ico.U16; break;
4660           case Ico_U32:  n = (ULong)con->Ico.U32; break;
4661           case Ico_U64:  n = (ULong)con->Ico.U64; break;
4662           case Ico_F64:  return False;
4663           case Ico_F32i: return False;
4664           case Ico_F64i: return False;
4665           case Ico_V128: return False;
4666           default: ppIRExpr(at); tl_assert(0);
4667        }
4668        /* VG_(printf)("%llx\n", n); */
4669        return (/*32*/    n == 0xFEFEFEFFULL
4670                /*32*/ || n == 0x80808080ULL
4671                /*32*/ || n == 0x7F7F7F7FULL
4672                /*64*/ || n == 0xFFFFFFFFFEFEFEFFULL
4673                /*64*/ || n == 0xFEFEFEFEFEFEFEFFULL
4674                /*64*/ || n == 0x0000000000008080ULL
4675                /*64*/ || n == 0x8080808080808080ULL
4676                /*64*/ || n == 0x0101010101010101ULL
4677               );
4678     }
4679     
4680     static Bool checkForBogusLiterals ( /*FLAT*/ IRStmt* st )
4681     {
4682        Int      i;
4683        IRExpr*  e;
4684        IRDirty* d;
4685        IRCAS*   cas;
4686        switch (st->tag) {
4687           case Ist_WrTmp:
4688              e = st->Ist.WrTmp.data;
4689              switch (e->tag) {
4690                 case Iex_Get:
4691                 case Iex_RdTmp:
4692                    return False;
4693                 case Iex_Const:
4694                    return isBogusAtom(e);
4695                 case Iex_Unop: 
4696                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Unop.arg);
4697                 case Iex_GetI:
4698                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.GetI.ix);
4699                 case Iex_Binop: 
4700                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Binop.arg1)
4701                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Binop.arg2);
4702                 case Iex_Triop: 
4703                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Triop.arg1)
4704                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Triop.arg2)
4705                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Triop.arg3);
4706                 case Iex_Qop: 
4707                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Qop.arg1)
4708                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Qop.arg2)
4709                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Qop.arg3)
4710                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Qop.arg4);
4711                 case Iex_Mux0X:
4712                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Mux0X.cond)
4713                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Mux0X.expr0)
4714                           || isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Mux0X.exprX);
4715                 case Iex_Load: 
4716                    return isBogusAtom(e->Iex.Load.addr);
4717                 case Iex_CCall:
4718                    for (i = 0; e->Iex.CCall.args[i]; i++)
4719                       if (isBogusAtom(e->Iex.CCall.args[i]))
4720                          return True;
4721                    return False;
4722                 default: 
4723                    goto unhandled;
4724              }
4725           case Ist_Dirty:
4726              d = st->Ist.Dirty.details;
4727              for (i = 0; d->args[i]; i++)
4728                 if (isBogusAtom(d->args[i]))
4729                    return True;
4730              if (d->guard && isBogusAtom(d->guard))
4731                 return True;
4732              if (d->mAddr && isBogusAtom(d->mAddr))
4733                 return True;
4734              return False;
4735           case Ist_Put:
4736              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.Put.data);
4737           case Ist_PutI:
4738              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.PutI.ix) 
4739                     || isBogusAtom(st->Ist.PutI.data);
4740           case Ist_Store:
4741              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.Store.addr) 
4742                     || isBogusAtom(st->Ist.Store.data);
4743           case Ist_Exit:
4744              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.Exit.guard);
4745           case Ist_AbiHint:
4746              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.AbiHint.base)
4747                     || isBogusAtom(st->Ist.AbiHint.nia);
4748           case Ist_NoOp:
4749           case Ist_IMark:
4750           case Ist_MBE:
4751              return False;
4752           case Ist_CAS:
4753              cas = st->Ist.CAS.details;
4754              return isBogusAtom(cas->addr)
4755                     || (cas->expdHi ? isBogusAtom(cas->expdHi) : False)
4756                     || isBogusAtom(cas->expdLo)
4757                     || (cas->dataHi ? isBogusAtom(cas->dataHi) : False)
4758                     || isBogusAtom(cas->dataLo);
4759           case Ist_LLSC:
4760              return isBogusAtom(st->Ist.LLSC.addr)
4761                     || (st->Ist.LLSC.storedata
4762                            ? isBogusAtom(st->Ist.LLSC.storedata)
4763                            : False);
4764           default: 
4765           unhandled:
4766              ppIRStmt(st);
4767              VG_(tool_panic)("hasBogusLiterals");
4768        }
4769     }
4770     
4771     
4772     IRSB* MC_(instrument) ( VgCallbackClosure* closure,
4773                             IRSB* sb_in, 
4774                             VexGuestLayout* layout, 
4775                             VexGuestExtents* vge,
4776                             IRType gWordTy, IRType hWordTy )
4777     {
4778        Bool    verboze = 0||False;
4779        Bool    bogus;
4780        Int     i, j, first_stmt;
4781        IRStmt* st;
4782        MCEnv   mce;
4783        IRSB*   sb_out;
4784     
4785        if (gWordTy != hWordTy) {
4786           /* We don't currently support this case. */
4787           VG_(tool_panic)("host/guest word size mismatch");
4788        }
4789     
4790        /* Check we're not completely nuts */
4791        tl_assert(sizeof(UWord)  == sizeof(void*));
4792        tl_assert(sizeof(Word)   == sizeof(void*));
4793        tl_assert(sizeof(Addr)   == sizeof(void*));
4794        tl_assert(sizeof(ULong)  == 8);
4795        tl_assert(sizeof(Long)   == 8);
4796        tl_assert(sizeof(Addr64) == 8);
4797        tl_assert(sizeof(UInt)   == 4);
4798        tl_assert(sizeof(Int)    == 4);
4799     
4800        tl_assert(MC_(clo_mc_level) >= 1 && MC_(clo_mc_level) <= 3);
4801     
4802        /* Set up SB */
4803        sb_out = deepCopyIRSBExceptStmts(sb_in);
4804     
4805        /* Set up the running environment.  Both .sb and .tmpMap are
4806           modified as we go along.  Note that tmps are added to both
4807           .sb->tyenv and .tmpMap together, so the valid index-set for
4808           those two arrays should always be identical. */
4809        VG_(memset)(&mce, 0, sizeof(mce));
4810        mce.sb             = sb_out;
4811        mce.trace          = verboze;
4812        mce.layout         = layout;
4813        mce.hWordTy        = hWordTy;
4814        mce.bogusLiterals  = False;
4815     
4816        mce.tmpMap = VG_(newXA)( VG_(malloc), "mc.MC_(instrument).1", VG_(free),
4817                                 sizeof(TempMapEnt));
4818        for (i = 0; i < sb_in->tyenv->types_used; i++) {
4819           TempMapEnt ent;
4820           ent.kind    = Orig;
4821           ent.shadowV = IRTemp_INVALID;
4822           ent.shadowB = IRTemp_INVALID;
4823           VG_(addToXA)( mce.tmpMap, &ent );
4824        }
4825        tl_assert( VG_(sizeXA)( mce.tmpMap ) == sb_in->tyenv->types_used );
4826     
4827        /* Make a preliminary inspection of the statements, to see if there
4828           are any dodgy-looking literals.  If there are, we generate
4829           extra-detailed (hence extra-expensive) instrumentation in
4830           places.  Scan the whole bb even if dodgyness is found earlier,
4831           so that the flatness assertion is applied to all stmts. */
4832     
4833        bogus = False;
4834     
4835        for (i = 0; i < sb_in->stmts_used; i++) {
4836     
4837           st = sb_in->stmts[i];
4838           tl_assert(st);
4839           tl_assert(isFlatIRStmt(st));
4840     
4841           if (!bogus) {
4842              bogus = checkForBogusLiterals(st);
4843              if (0 && bogus) {
4844                 VG_(printf)("bogus: ");
4845                 ppIRStmt(st);
4846                 VG_(printf)("\n");
4847              }
4848           }
4849     
4850        }
4851     
4852        mce.bogusLiterals = bogus;
4853     
4854        /* Copy verbatim any IR preamble preceding the first IMark */
4855     
4856        tl_assert(mce.sb == sb_out);
4857        tl_assert(mce.sb != sb_in);
4858     
4859        i = 0;
4860        while (i < sb_in->stmts_used && sb_in->stmts[i]->tag != Ist_IMark) {
4861     
4862           st = sb_in->stmts[i];
4863           tl_assert(st);
4864           tl_assert(isFlatIRStmt(st));
4865     
4866           stmt( 'C', &mce, sb_in->stmts[i] );
4867           i++;
4868        }
4869     
4870        /* Nasty problem.  IR optimisation of the pre-instrumented IR may
4871           cause the IR following the preamble to contain references to IR
4872           temporaries defined in the preamble.  Because the preamble isn't
4873           instrumented, these temporaries don't have any shadows.
4874           Nevertheless uses of them following the preamble will cause
4875           memcheck to generate references to their shadows.  End effect is
4876           to cause IR sanity check failures, due to references to
4877           non-existent shadows.  This is only evident for the complex
4878           preambles used for function wrapping on TOC-afflicted platforms
4879           (ppc64-linux, ppc32-aix5, ppc64-aix5).
4880     
4881           The following loop therefore scans the preamble looking for
4882           assignments to temporaries.  For each one found it creates an
4883           assignment to the corresponding (V) shadow temp, marking it as
4884           'defined'.  This is the same resulting IR as if the main
4885           instrumentation loop before had been applied to the statement
4886           'tmp = CONSTANT'.
4887     
4888           Similarly, if origin tracking is enabled, we must generate an
4889           assignment for the corresponding origin (B) shadow, claiming
4890           no-origin, as appropriate for a defined value.
4891        */
4892        for (j = 0; j < i; j++) {
4893           if (sb_in->stmts[j]->tag == Ist_WrTmp) {
4894              /* findShadowTmpV checks its arg is an original tmp;
4895                 no need to assert that here. */
4896              IRTemp tmp_o = sb_in->stmts[j]->Ist.WrTmp.tmp;
4897              IRTemp tmp_v = findShadowTmpV(&mce, tmp_o);
4898              IRType ty_v  = typeOfIRTemp(sb_out->tyenv, tmp_v);
4899              assign( 'V', &mce, tmp_v, definedOfType( ty_v ) );
4900              if (MC_(clo_mc_level) == 3) {
4901                 IRTemp tmp_b = findShadowTmpB(&mce, tmp_o);
4902                 tl_assert(typeOfIRTemp(sb_out->tyenv, tmp_b) == Ity_I32);
4903                 assign( 'B', &mce, tmp_b, mkU32(0)/* UNKNOWN ORIGIN */);
4904              }
4905              if (0) {
4906                 VG_(printf)("create shadow tmp(s) for preamble tmp [%d] ty ", j);
4907                 ppIRType( ty_v );
4908                 VG_(printf)("\n");
4909              }
4910           }
4911        }
4912     
4913        /* Iterate over the remaining stmts to generate instrumentation. */
4914     
4915        tl_assert(sb_in->stmts_used > 0);
4916        tl_assert(i >= 0);
4917        tl_assert(i < sb_in->stmts_used);
4918        tl_assert(sb_in->stmts[i]->tag == Ist_IMark);
4919     
4920        for (/* use current i*/; i < sb_in->stmts_used; i++) {
4921     
4922           st = sb_in->stmts[i];
4923           first_stmt = sb_out->stmts_used;
4924     
4925           if (verboze) {
4926              VG_(printf)("\n");
4927              ppIRStmt(st);
4928              VG_(printf)("\n");
4929           }
4930     
4931           if (MC_(clo_mc_level) == 3) {
4932              /* See comments on case Ist_CAS below. */
4933              if (st->tag != Ist_CAS) 
4934                 schemeS( &mce, st );
4935           }
4936     
4937           /* Generate instrumentation code for each stmt ... */
4938     
4939           switch (st->tag) {
4940     
4941              case Ist_WrTmp:
4942                 assign( 'V', &mce, findShadowTmpV(&mce, st->Ist.WrTmp.tmp), 
4943                                    expr2vbits( &mce, st->Ist.WrTmp.data) );
4944                 break;
4945     
4946              case Ist_Put:
4947                 do_shadow_PUT( &mce, 
4948                                st->Ist.Put.offset,
4949                                st->Ist.Put.data,
4950                                NULL /* shadow atom */ );
4951                 break;
4952     
4953              case Ist_PutI:
4954                 do_shadow_PUTI( &mce, 
4955                                 st->Ist.PutI.descr,
4956                                 st->Ist.PutI.ix,
4957                                 st->Ist.PutI.bias,
4958                                 st->Ist.PutI.data );
4959                 break;
4960     
4961              case Ist_Store:
4962                 do_shadow_Store( &mce, st->Ist.Store.end,
4963                                        st->Ist.Store.addr, 0/* addr bias */,
4964                                        st->Ist.Store.data,
4965                                        NULL /* shadow data */,
4966                                        NULL/*guard*/ );
4967                 break;
4968     
4969              case Ist_Exit:
4970                 complainIfUndefined( &mce, st->Ist.Exit.guard );
4971                 break;
4972     
4973              case Ist_IMark:
4974                 break;
4975     
4976              case Ist_NoOp:
4977              case Ist_MBE:
4978                 break;
4979     
4980              case Ist_Dirty:
4981                 do_shadow_Dirty( &mce, st->Ist.Dirty.details );
4982                 break;
4983     
4984              case Ist_AbiHint:
4985                 do_AbiHint( &mce, st->Ist.AbiHint.base,
4986                                   st->Ist.AbiHint.len,
4987                                   st->Ist.AbiHint.nia );
4988                 break;
4989     
4990              case Ist_CAS:
4991                 do_shadow_CAS( &mce, st->Ist.CAS.details );
4992                 /* Note, do_shadow_CAS copies the CAS itself to the output
4993                    block, because it needs to add instrumentation both
4994                    before and after it.  Hence skip the copy below.  Also
4995                    skip the origin-tracking stuff (call to schemeS) above,
4996                    since that's all tangled up with it too; do_shadow_CAS
4997                    does it all. */
4998                 break;
4999     
5000              case Ist_LLSC:
5001                 do_shadow_LLSC( &mce,
5002                                 st->Ist.LLSC.end,
5003                                 st->Ist.LLSC.result,
5004                                 st->Ist.LLSC.addr,
5005                                 st->Ist.LLSC.storedata );
5006                 break;
5007     
5008              default:
5009                 VG_(printf)("\n");
5010                 ppIRStmt(st);
5011                 VG_(printf)("\n");
5012                 VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck: unhandled IRStmt");
5013     
5014           } /* switch (st->tag) */
5015     
5016           if (0 && verboze) {
5017              for (j = first_stmt; j < sb_out->stmts_used; j++) {
5018                 VG_(printf)("   ");
5019                 ppIRStmt(sb_out->stmts[j]);
5020                 VG_(printf)("\n");
5021              }
5022              VG_(printf)("\n");
5023           }
5024     
5025           /* ... and finally copy the stmt itself to the output.  Except,
5026              skip the copy of IRCASs; see comments on case Ist_CAS
5027              above. */
5028           if (st->tag != Ist_CAS)
5029              stmt('C', &mce, st);
5030        }
5031     
5032        /* Now we need to complain if the jump target is undefined. */
5033        first_stmt = sb_out->stmts_used;
5034     
5035        if (verboze) {
5036           VG_(printf)("sb_in->next = ");
5037           ppIRExpr(sb_in->next);
5038           VG_(printf)("\n\n");
5039        }
5040     
5041        complainIfUndefined( &mce, sb_in->next );
5042     
5043        if (0 && verboze) {
5044           for (j = first_stmt; j < sb_out->stmts_used; j++) {
5045              VG_(printf)("   ");
5046              ppIRStmt(sb_out->stmts[j]);
5047              VG_(printf)("\n");
5048           }
5049           VG_(printf)("\n");
5050        }
5051     
5052        /* If this fails, there's been some serious snafu with tmp management,
5053           that should be investigated. */
5054        tl_assert( VG_(sizeXA)( mce.tmpMap ) == mce.sb->tyenv->types_used );
5055        VG_(deleteXA)( mce.tmpMap );
5056     
5057        tl_assert(mce.sb == sb_out);
5058        return sb_out;
5059     }
5060     
5061     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
5062     /*--- Post-tree-build final tidying                        ---*/
5063     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
5064     
5065     /* This exploits the observation that Memcheck often produces
5066        repeated conditional calls of the form
5067     
5068        Dirty G MC_(helperc_value_check0/1/4/8_fail)(UInt otag)
5069     
5070        with the same guard expression G guarding the same helper call.
5071        The second and subsequent calls are redundant.  This usually
5072        results from instrumentation of guest code containing multiple
5073        memory references at different constant offsets from the same base
5074        register.  After optimisation of the instrumentation, you get a
5075        test for the definedness of the base register for each memory
5076        reference, which is kinda pointless.  MC_(final_tidy) therefore
5077        looks for such repeated calls and removes all but the first. */
5078     
5079     /* A struct for recording which (helper, guard) pairs we have already
5080        seen. */
5081     typedef
5082        struct { void* entry; IRExpr* guard; }
5083        Pair;
5084     
5085     /* Return True if e1 and e2 definitely denote the same value (used to
5086        compare guards).  Return False if unknown; False is the safe
5087        answer.  Since guest registers and guest memory do not have the
5088        SSA property we must return False if any Gets or Loads appear in
5089        the expression. */
5090     
5091     static Bool sameIRValue ( IRExpr* e1, IRExpr* e2 )
5092     {
5093        if (e1->tag != e2->tag)
5094           return False;
5095        switch (e1->tag) {
5096           case Iex_Const:
5097              return eqIRConst( e1->Iex.Const.con, e2->Iex.Const.con );
5098           case Iex_Binop:
5099              return e1->Iex.Binop.op == e2->Iex.Binop.op 
5100                     && sameIRValue(e1->Iex.Binop.arg1, e2->Iex.Binop.arg1)
5101                     && sameIRValue(e1->Iex.Binop.arg2, e2->Iex.Binop.arg2);
5102           case Iex_Unop:
5103              return e1->Iex.Unop.op == e2->Iex.Unop.op 
5104                     && sameIRValue(e1->Iex.Unop.arg, e2->Iex.Unop.arg);
5105           case Iex_RdTmp:
5106              return e1->Iex.RdTmp.tmp == e2->Iex.RdTmp.tmp;
5107           case Iex_Mux0X:
5108              return sameIRValue( e1->Iex.Mux0X.cond, e2->Iex.Mux0X.cond )
5109                     && sameIRValue( e1->Iex.Mux0X.expr0, e2->Iex.Mux0X.expr0 )
5110                     && sameIRValue( e1->Iex.Mux0X.exprX, e2->Iex.Mux0X.exprX );
5111           case Iex_Qop:
5112           case Iex_Triop:
5113           case Iex_CCall:
5114              /* be lazy.  Could define equality for these, but they never
5115                 appear to be used. */
5116              return False;
5117           case Iex_Get:
5118           case Iex_GetI:
5119           case Iex_Load:
5120              /* be conservative - these may not give the same value each
5121                 time */
5122              return False;
5123           case Iex_Binder:
5124              /* should never see this */
5125              /* fallthrough */
5126           default:
5127              VG_(printf)("mc_translate.c: sameIRValue: unhandled: ");
5128              ppIRExpr(e1); 
5129              VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:sameIRValue");
5130              return False;
5131        }
5132     }
5133     
5134     /* See if 'pairs' already has an entry for (entry, guard).  Return
5135        True if so.  If not, add an entry. */
5136     
5137     static 
5138     Bool check_or_add ( XArray* /*of Pair*/ pairs, IRExpr* guard, void* entry )
5139     {
5140        Pair  p;
5141        Pair* pp;
5142        Int   i, n = VG_(sizeXA)( pairs );
5143        for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5144           pp = VG_(indexXA)( pairs, i );
5145           if (pp->entry == entry && sameIRValue(pp->guard, guard))
5146              return True;
5147        }
5148        p.guard = guard;
5149        p.entry = entry;
5150        VG_(addToXA)( pairs, &p );
5151        return False;
5152     }
5153     
5154     static Bool is_helperc_value_checkN_fail ( HChar* name )
5155     {
5156        return
5157           0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check0_fail_no_o)")
5158           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check1_fail_no_o)")
5159           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check4_fail_no_o)")
5160           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check8_fail_no_o)")
5161           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check0_fail_w_o)")
5162           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check1_fail_w_o)")
5163           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check4_fail_w_o)")
5164           || 0==VG_(strcmp)(name, "MC_(helperc_value_check8_fail_w_o)");
5165     }
5166     
5167     IRSB* MC_(final_tidy) ( IRSB* sb_in )
5168     {
5169        Int i;
5170        IRStmt*   st;
5171        IRDirty*  di;
5172        IRExpr*   guard;
5173        IRCallee* cee;
5174        Bool      alreadyPresent;
5175        XArray*   pairs = VG_(newXA)( VG_(malloc), "mc.ft.1",
5176                                      VG_(free), sizeof(Pair) );
5177        /* Scan forwards through the statements.  Each time a call to one
5178           of the relevant helpers is seen, check if we have made a
5179           previous call to the same helper using the same guard
5180           expression, and if so, delete the call. */
5181        for (i = 0; i < sb_in->stmts_used; i++) {
5182           st = sb_in->stmts[i];
5183           tl_assert(st);
5184           if (st->tag != Ist_Dirty)
5185              continue;
5186           di = st->Ist.Dirty.details;
5187           guard = di->guard;
5188           if (!guard)
5189              continue;
5190           if (0) { ppIRExpr(guard); VG_(printf)("\n"); }
5191           cee = di->cee;
5192           if (!is_helperc_value_checkN_fail( cee->name )) 
5193              continue;
5194            /* Ok, we have a call to helperc_value_check0/1/4/8_fail with
5195               guard 'guard'.  Check if we have already seen a call to this
5196               function with the same guard.  If so, delete it.  If not,
5197               add it to the set of calls we do know about. */
5198           alreadyPresent = check_or_add( pairs, guard, cee->addr );
5199           if (alreadyPresent) {
5200              sb_in->stmts[i] = IRStmt_NoOp();
5201              if (0) VG_(printf)("XX\n");
5202           }
5203        }
5204        VG_(deleteXA)( pairs );
5205        return sb_in;
5206     }

5210     /*--- Origin tracking stuff                                ---*/

5212     
5213     /* Almost identical to findShadowTmpV. */
5214     static IRTemp findShadowTmpB ( MCEnv* mce, IRTemp orig )
5215     {
5216        TempMapEnt* ent;
5217        /* VG_(indexXA) range-checks 'orig', hence no need to check
5218           here. */
5219        ent = (TempMapEnt*)VG_(indexXA)( mce->tmpMap, (Word)orig );
5220        tl_assert(ent->kind == Orig);
5221        if (ent->shadowB == IRTemp_INVALID) {
5222           IRTemp tmpB
5223             = newTemp( mce, Ity_I32, BSh );
5224           /* newTemp may cause mce->tmpMap to resize, hence previous results
5225              from VG_(indexXA) are invalid. */
5226           ent = (TempMapEnt*)VG_(indexXA)( mce->tmpMap, (Word)orig );
5227           tl_assert(ent->kind == Orig);
5228           tl_assert(ent->shadowB == IRTemp_INVALID);
5229           ent->shadowB = tmpB;
5230        }
5231        return ent->shadowB;
5232     }
