5234     static IRAtom* gen_maxU32 ( MCEnv* mce, IRAtom* b1, IRAtom* b2 )
5235     {
5236        return assignNew( 'B', mce, Ity_I32, binop(Iop_Max32U, b1, b2) );
5237     }
5238     
5239     static IRAtom* gen_load_b ( MCEnv* mce, Int szB, 
5240                                 IRAtom* baseaddr, Int offset )
5241     {
5242        void*    hFun;
5243        HChar*   hName;
5244        IRTemp   bTmp;
5245        IRDirty* di;
5246        IRType   aTy   = typeOfIRExpr( mce->sb->tyenv, baseaddr );
5247        IROp     opAdd = aTy == Ity_I32 ? Iop_Add32 : Iop_Add64;
5248        IRAtom*  ea    = baseaddr;
5249        if (offset != 0) {
5250           IRAtom* off = aTy == Ity_I32 ? mkU32( offset )
5251                                        : mkU64( (Long)(Int)offset );
5252           ea = assignNew( 'B', mce, aTy, binop(opAdd, ea, off));
5253        }
5254        bTmp = newTemp(mce, mce->hWordTy, BSh);
5255     
5256        switch (szB) {
5257           case 1: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_load1);
5258                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_load1)";
5259                   break;
5260           case 2: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_load2);
5261                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_load2)";
5262                   break;
5263           case 4: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_load4);
5264                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_load4)";
5265                   break;
5266           case 8: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_load8);
5267                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_load8)";
5268                   break;
5269           case 16: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_load16);
5270                    hName = "MC_(helperc_b_load16)";
5271                    break;
5272           default:
5273              VG_(printf)("mc_translate.c: gen_load_b: unhandled szB == %d\n", szB);
5274              tl_assert(0);
5275        }
5276        di = unsafeIRDirty_1_N(
5277                bTmp, 1/*regparms*/, hName, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( hFun ),
5278                mkIRExprVec_1( ea )
5279             );
5280        /* no need to mess with any annotations.  This call accesses
5281           neither guest state nor guest memory. */
5282        stmt( 'B', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(di) );
5283        if (mce->hWordTy == Ity_I64) {
5284           /* 64-bit host */
5285           IRTemp bTmp32 = newTemp(mce, Ity_I32, BSh);
5286           assign( 'B', mce, bTmp32, unop(Iop_64to32, mkexpr(bTmp)) );
5287           return mkexpr(bTmp32);
5288        } else {
5289           /* 32-bit host */
5290           return mkexpr(bTmp);
5291        }
5292     }
5293     
5294     /* Generate a shadow store.  guard :: Ity_I1 controls whether the
5295        store really happens; NULL means it unconditionally does. */
5296     static void gen_store_b ( MCEnv* mce, Int szB,
5297                               IRAtom* baseaddr, Int offset, IRAtom* dataB,
5298                               IRAtom* guard )
5299     {
5300        void*    hFun;
5301        HChar*   hName;
5302        IRDirty* di;
5303        IRType   aTy   = typeOfIRExpr( mce->sb->tyenv, baseaddr );
5304        IROp     opAdd = aTy == Ity_I32 ? Iop_Add32 : Iop_Add64;
5305        IRAtom*  ea    = baseaddr;
5306        if (guard) {
5307           tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, guard));
5308           tl_assert(typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, guard) == Ity_I1);
5309        }
5310        if (offset != 0) {
5311           IRAtom* off = aTy == Ity_I32 ? mkU32( offset )
5312                                        : mkU64( (Long)(Int)offset );
5313           ea = assignNew(  'B', mce, aTy, binop(opAdd, ea, off));
5314        }
5315        if (mce->hWordTy == Ity_I64)
5316           dataB = assignNew( 'B', mce, Ity_I64, unop(Iop_32Uto64, dataB));
5317     
5318        switch (szB) {
5319           case 1: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_store1);
5320                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_store1)";
5321                   break;
5322           case 2: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_store2);
5323                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_store2)";
5324                   break;
5325           case 4: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_store4);
5326                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_store4)";
5327                   break;
5328           case 8: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_store8);
5329                   hName = "MC_(helperc_b_store8)";
5330                   break;
5331           case 16: hFun  = (void*)&MC_(helperc_b_store16);
5332                    hName = "MC_(helperc_b_store16)";
5333                    break;
5334           default:
5335              tl_assert(0);
5336        }
5337        di = unsafeIRDirty_0_N( 2/*regparms*/,
5338                hName, VG_(fnptr_to_fnentry)( hFun ),
5339                mkIRExprVec_2( ea, dataB )
5340             );
5341        /* no need to mess with any annotations.  This call accesses
5342           neither guest state nor guest memory. */
5343        if (guard) di->guard = guard;
5344        stmt( 'B', mce, IRStmt_Dirty(di) );
5345     }
5346     
5347     static IRAtom* narrowTo32 ( MCEnv* mce, IRAtom* e ) {
5348        IRType eTy = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, e);
5349        if (eTy == Ity_I64)
5350           return assignNew( 'B', mce, Ity_I32, unop(Iop_64to32, e) );
5351        if (eTy == Ity_I32)
5352           return e;
5353        tl_assert(0);
5354     }
5355     
5356     static IRAtom* zWidenFrom32 ( MCEnv* mce, IRType dstTy, IRAtom* e ) {
5357        IRType eTy = typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, e);
5358        tl_assert(eTy == Ity_I32);
5359        if (dstTy == Ity_I64)
5360           return assignNew( 'B', mce, Ity_I64, unop(Iop_32Uto64, e) );
5361        tl_assert(0);
5362     }
5363     
5364     
5365     static IRAtom* schemeE ( MCEnv* mce, IRExpr* e )
5366     {
5367        tl_assert(MC_(clo_mc_level) == 3);
5368     
5369        switch (e->tag) {
5370     
5371           case Iex_GetI: {
5372              IRRegArray* descr_b;
5373              IRAtom      *t1, *t2, *t3, *t4;
5374              IRRegArray* descr      = e->Iex.GetI.descr;
5375              IRType equivIntTy 
5376                 = MC_(get_otrack_reg_array_equiv_int_type)(descr);
5377              /* If this array is unshadowable for whatever reason, use the
5378                 usual approximation. */
5379              if (equivIntTy == Ity_INVALID)
5380                 return mkU32(0);
5381              tl_assert(sizeofIRType(equivIntTy) >= 4);
5382              tl_assert(sizeofIRType(equivIntTy) == sizeofIRType(descr->elemTy));
5383              descr_b = mkIRRegArray( descr->base + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB,
5384                                      equivIntTy, descr->nElems );
5385              /* Do a shadow indexed get of the same size, giving t1.  Take
5386                 the bottom 32 bits of it, giving t2.  Compute into t3 the
5387                 origin for the index (almost certainly zero, but there's
5388                 no harm in being completely general here, since iropt will
5389                 remove any useless code), and fold it in, giving a final
5390                 value t4. */
5391              t1 = assignNew( 'B', mce, equivIntTy, 
5392                               IRExpr_GetI( descr_b, e->Iex.GetI.ix, 
5393                                                     e->Iex.GetI.bias ));
5394              t2 = narrowTo32( mce, t1 );
5395              t3 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.GetI.ix );
5396              t4 = gen_maxU32( mce, t2, t3 );
5397              return t4;
5398           }
5399           case Iex_CCall: {
5400              Int i;
5401              IRAtom*  here;
5402              IRExpr** args = e->Iex.CCall.args;
5403              IRAtom*  curr = mkU32(0);
5404              for (i = 0; args[i]; i++) {
5405                 tl_assert(i < 32);
5406                 tl_assert(isOriginalAtom(mce, args[i]));
5407                 /* Only take notice of this arg if the callee's
5408                    mc-exclusion mask does not say it is to be excluded. */
5409                 if (e->Iex.CCall.cee->mcx_mask & (1<<i)) {
5410                    /* the arg is to be excluded from definedness checking.
5411                       Do nothing. */
5412                    if (0) VG_(printf)("excluding %s(%d)\n",
5413                                       e->Iex.CCall.cee->name, i);
5414                 } else {
5415                    /* calculate the arg's definedness, and pessimistically
5416                       merge it in. */
5417                    here = schemeE( mce, args[i] );
5418                    curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5419                 }
5420              }
5421              return curr;
5422           }
5423           case Iex_Load: {
5424              Int dszB;
5425              dszB = sizeofIRType(e->Iex.Load.ty);
5426              /* assert that the B value for the address is already
5427                 available (somewhere) */
5428              tl_assert(isIRAtom(e->Iex.Load.addr));
5429              tl_assert(mce->hWordTy == Ity_I32 || mce->hWordTy == Ity_I64);
5430              return gen_load_b( mce, dszB, e->Iex.Load.addr, 0 );
5431           }
5432           case Iex_Mux0X: {
5433              IRAtom* b1 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Mux0X.cond );
5434              IRAtom* b2 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Mux0X.expr0 );
5435              IRAtom* b3 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Mux0X.exprX );
5436              return gen_maxU32( mce, b1, gen_maxU32( mce, b2, b3 ));
5437           }
5438           case Iex_Qop: {
5439              IRAtom* b1 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Qop.arg1 );
5440              IRAtom* b2 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Qop.arg2 );
5441              IRAtom* b3 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Qop.arg3 );
5442              IRAtom* b4 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Qop.arg4 );
5443              return gen_maxU32( mce, gen_maxU32( mce, b1, b2 ),
5444                                      gen_maxU32( mce, b3, b4 ) );
5445           }
5446           case Iex_Triop: {
5447              IRAtom* b1 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Triop.arg1 );
5448              IRAtom* b2 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Triop.arg2 );
5449              IRAtom* b3 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Triop.arg3 );
5450              return gen_maxU32( mce, b1, gen_maxU32( mce, b2, b3 ) );
5451           }
5452           case Iex_Binop: {
5453              switch (e->Iex.Binop.op) {
5454                 case Iop_CasCmpEQ8:  case Iop_CasCmpNE8:
5455                 case Iop_CasCmpEQ16: case Iop_CasCmpNE16:
5456                 case Iop_CasCmpEQ32: case Iop_CasCmpNE32:
5457                 case Iop_CasCmpEQ64: case Iop_CasCmpNE64:
5458                    /* Just say these all produce a defined result,
5459                       regardless of their arguments.  See
5460                       COMMENT_ON_CasCmpEQ in this file. */
5461                    return mkU32(0);
5462                 default: {
5463                    IRAtom* b1 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Binop.arg1 );
5464                    IRAtom* b2 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Binop.arg2 );
5465                    return gen_maxU32( mce, b1, b2 );
5466                 }
5467              }
5468              tl_assert(0);
5469              /*NOTREACHED*/
5470           }
5471           case Iex_Unop: {
5472              IRAtom* b1 = schemeE( mce, e->Iex.Unop.arg );
5473              return b1;
5474           }
5475           case Iex_Const:
5476              return mkU32(0);
5477           case Iex_RdTmp:
5478              return mkexpr( findShadowTmpB( mce, e->Iex.RdTmp.tmp ));
5479           case Iex_Get: {
5480              Int b_offset = MC_(get_otrack_shadow_offset)( 
5481                                e->Iex.Get.offset,
5482                                sizeofIRType(e->Iex.Get.ty) 
5483                             );
5484              tl_assert(b_offset >= -1
5485                        && b_offset <= mce->layout->total_sizeB -4);
5486              if (b_offset >= 0) {
5487                 /* FIXME: this isn't an atom! */
5488                 return IRExpr_Get( b_offset + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB,
5489                                    Ity_I32 );
5490              }
5491              return mkU32(0);
5492           }
5493           default:
5494              VG_(printf)("mc_translate.c: schemeE: unhandled: ");
5495              ppIRExpr(e); 
5496              VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:schemeE");
5497        }
5498     }
5499     
5500     
5501     static void do_origins_Dirty ( MCEnv* mce, IRDirty* d )
5502     {
5503        // This is a hacked version of do_shadow_Dirty
5504        Int       i, n, toDo, gSz, gOff;
5505        IRAtom    *here, *curr;
5506        IRTemp    dst;
5507     
5508        /* First check the guard. */
5509        curr = schemeE( mce, d->guard );
5510     
5511        /* Now round up all inputs and maxU32 over them. */
5512     
5513        /* Inputs: unmasked args */
5514        for (i = 0; d->args[i]; i++) {
5515           if (d->cee->mcx_mask & (1<<i)) {
5516              /* ignore this arg */
5517           } else {
5518              here = schemeE( mce, d->args[i] );
5519              curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5520           }
5521        }
5522     
5523        /* Inputs: guest state that we read. */
5524        for (i = 0; i < d->nFxState; i++) {
5525           tl_assert(d->fxState[i].fx != Ifx_None);
5526           if (d->fxState[i].fx == Ifx_Write)
5527              continue;
5528     
5529           /* Ignore any sections marked as 'always defined'. */
5530           if (isAlwaysDefd(mce, d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size )) {
5531              if (0)
5532              VG_(printf)("memcheck: Dirty gst: ignored off %d, sz %d\n",
5533                          d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size );
5534              continue;
5535           }
5536     
5537           /* This state element is read or modified.  So we need to
5538              consider it.  If larger than 4 bytes, deal with it in 4-byte
5539              chunks. */
5540           gSz  = d->fxState[i].size;
5541           gOff = d->fxState[i].offset;
5542           tl_assert(gSz > 0);
5543           while (True) {
5544              Int b_offset;
5545              if (gSz == 0) break;
5546              n = gSz <= 4 ? gSz : 4;
5547              /* update 'curr' with maxU32 of the state slice 
5548                 gOff .. gOff+n-1 */
5549              b_offset = MC_(get_otrack_shadow_offset)(gOff, 4);
5550              if (b_offset != -1) {
5551                 here = assignNew( 'B',mce,
5552                                    Ity_I32,
5553                                    IRExpr_Get(b_offset + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB,
5554                                               Ity_I32));
5555                 curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5556              }
5557              gSz -= n;
5558              gOff += n;
5559           }
5560     
5561        }
5562     
5563        /* Inputs: memory */
5564     
5565        if (d->mFx != Ifx_None) {
5566           /* Because we may do multiple shadow loads/stores from the same
5567              base address, it's best to do a single test of its
5568              definedness right now.  Post-instrumentation optimisation
5569              should remove all but this test. */
5570           tl_assert(d->mAddr);
5571           here = schemeE( mce, d->mAddr );
5572           curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5573        }
5574     
5575        /* Deal with memory inputs (reads or modifies) */
5576        if (d->mFx == Ifx_Read || d->mFx == Ifx_Modify) {
5577           toDo   = d->mSize;
5578           /* chew off 32-bit chunks.  We don't care about the endianness
5579              since it's all going to be condensed down to a single bit,
5580              but nevertheless choose an endianness which is hopefully
5581              native to the platform. */
5582           while (toDo >= 4) {
5583              here = gen_load_b( mce, 4, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo );
5584              curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5585              toDo -= 4;
5586           }
5587           /* handle possible 16-bit excess */
5588           while (toDo >= 2) {
5589              here = gen_load_b( mce, 2, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo );
5590              curr = gen_maxU32( mce, curr, here );
5591              toDo -= 2;
5592           }
5593           tl_assert(toDo == 0); /* also need to handle 1-byte excess */
5594        }
5595     
5596        /* Whew!  So curr is a 32-bit B-value which should give an origin
5597           of some use if any of the inputs to the helper are undefined.
5598           Now we need to re-distribute the results to all destinations. */
5599     
5600        /* Outputs: the destination temporary, if there is one. */
5601        if (d->tmp != IRTemp_INVALID) {
5602           dst   = findShadowTmpB(mce, d->tmp);
5603           assign( 'V', mce, dst, curr );
5604        }
5605     
5606        /* Outputs: guest state that we write or modify. */
5607        for (i = 0; i < d->nFxState; i++) {
5608           tl_assert(d->fxState[i].fx != Ifx_None);
5609           if (d->fxState[i].fx == Ifx_Read)
5610              continue;
5611     
5612           /* Ignore any sections marked as 'always defined'. */
5613           if (isAlwaysDefd(mce, d->fxState[i].offset, d->fxState[i].size ))
5614              continue;
5615     
5616           /* This state element is written or modified.  So we need to
5617              consider it.  If larger than 4 bytes, deal with it in 4-byte
5618              chunks. */
5619           gSz  = d->fxState[i].size;
5620           gOff = d->fxState[i].offset;
5621           tl_assert(gSz > 0);
5622           while (True) {
5623              Int b_offset;
5624              if (gSz == 0) break;
5625              n = gSz <= 4 ? gSz : 4;
5626              /* Write 'curr' to the state slice gOff .. gOff+n-1 */
5627              b_offset = MC_(get_otrack_shadow_offset)(gOff, 4);
5628              if (b_offset != -1) {
5629                stmt( 'B', mce, IRStmt_Put(b_offset + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB,
5630                                           curr ));
5631              }
5632              gSz -= n;
5633              gOff += n;
5634           }
5635        }
5636     
5637        /* Outputs: memory that we write or modify.  Same comments about
5638           endianness as above apply. */
5639        if (d->mFx == Ifx_Write || d->mFx == Ifx_Modify) {
5640           toDo   = d->mSize;
5641           /* chew off 32-bit chunks */
5642           while (toDo >= 4) {
5643              gen_store_b( mce, 4, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo, curr,
5644                           NULL/*guard*/ );
5645              toDo -= 4;
5646           }
5647           /* handle possible 16-bit excess */
5648           while (toDo >= 2) {
5649             gen_store_b( mce, 2, d->mAddr, d->mSize - toDo, curr,
5650                          NULL/*guard*/ );
5651              toDo -= 2;
5652           }
5653           tl_assert(toDo == 0); /* also need to handle 1-byte excess */
5654        }
5655     }

5658     static void do_origins_Store ( MCEnv* mce,
5659                                    IREndness stEnd,
5660                                    IRExpr* stAddr,
5661                                    IRExpr* stData )
5662     {
5663        Int     dszB;
5664        IRAtom* dataB;
5665        /* assert that the B value for the address is already available
5666           (somewhere), since the call to schemeE will want to see it.
5667           XXXX how does this actually ensure that?? */
5668        tl_assert(isIRAtom(stAddr));
5669        tl_assert(isIRAtom(stData));
5670        dszB  = sizeofIRType( typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, stData ) );
5671        dataB = schemeE( mce, stData );
5672        gen_store_b( mce, dszB, stAddr, 0/*offset*/, dataB,
5673                          NULL/*guard*/ );
5674     }

5676     
5677     static void schemeS ( MCEnv* mce, IRStmt* st )
5678     {
5679        tl_assert(MC_(clo_mc_level) == 3);
5680     
5681        switch (st->tag) {
5682     
5683           case Ist_AbiHint:
5684              /* The value-check instrumenter handles this - by arranging
5685                 to pass the address of the next instruction to
5686                 MC_(helperc_MAKE_STACK_UNINIT).  This is all that needs to
5687                 happen for origin tracking w.r.t. AbiHints.  So there is
5688                 nothing to do here. */
5689              break;
5690     
5691           case Ist_PutI: {
5692              IRRegArray* descr_b;
5693              IRAtom      *t1, *t2, *t3, *t4;
5694              IRRegArray* descr = st->Ist.PutI.descr;
5695              IRType equivIntTy
5696                 = MC_(get_otrack_reg_array_equiv_int_type)(descr);
5697              /* If this array is unshadowable for whatever reason,
5698                 generate no code. */
5699              if (equivIntTy == Ity_INVALID)
5700                 break;
5701              tl_assert(sizeofIRType(equivIntTy) >= 4);
5702              tl_assert(sizeofIRType(equivIntTy) == sizeofIRType(descr->elemTy));
5703              descr_b
5704                 = mkIRRegArray( descr->base + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB,
5705                                 equivIntTy, descr->nElems );
5706              /* Compute a value to Put - the conjoinment of the origin for
5707                 the data to be Put-ted (obviously) and of the index value
5708                 (not so obviously). */
5709              t1 = schemeE( mce, st->Ist.PutI.data );
5710              t2 = schemeE( mce, st->Ist.PutI.ix );
5711              t3 = gen_maxU32( mce, t1, t2 );
5712              t4 = zWidenFrom32( mce, equivIntTy, t3 );
5713              stmt( 'B', mce, IRStmt_PutI( descr_b, st->Ist.PutI.ix,
5714                                           st->Ist.PutI.bias, t4 ));
5715              break;
5716           }
5717     
5718           case Ist_Dirty:
5719              do_origins_Dirty( mce, st->Ist.Dirty.details );
5720              break;
5721     
5722           case Ist_Store:
5723              do_origins_Store( mce, st->Ist.Store.end,
5724                                     st->Ist.Store.addr,
5725                                     st->Ist.Store.data );
5726              break;
5727     
5728           case Ist_LLSC: {
5729              /* In short: treat a load-linked like a normal load followed
5730                 by an assignment of the loaded (shadow) data the result
5731                 temporary.  Treat a store-conditional like a normal store,
5732                 and mark the result temporary as defined. */
5733              if (st->Ist.LLSC.storedata == NULL) {
5734                 /* Load Linked */
5735                 IRType resTy 
5736                    = typeOfIRTemp(mce->sb->tyenv, st->Ist.LLSC.result);
5737                 IRExpr* vanillaLoad
5738                    = IRExpr_Load(st->Ist.LLSC.end, resTy, st->Ist.LLSC.addr);
5739                 tl_assert(resTy == Ity_I64 || resTy == Ity_I32
5740                           || resTy == Ity_I16 || resTy == Ity_I8);
5741                 assign( 'B', mce, findShadowTmpB(mce, st->Ist.LLSC.result),
5742                                   schemeE(mce, vanillaLoad));
5743              } else {
5744                 /* Store conditional */
5745                 do_origins_Store( mce, st->Ist.LLSC.end,
5746                                        st->Ist.LLSC.addr,
5747                                        st->Ist.LLSC.storedata );
5748                 /* For the rationale behind this, see comments at the
5749                    place where the V-shadow for .result is constructed, in
5750                    do_shadow_LLSC.  In short, we regard .result as
5751                    always-defined. */
5752                 assign( 'B', mce, findShadowTmpB(mce, st->Ist.LLSC.result),
5753                                   mkU32(0) );
5754              }
5755              break;
5756           }
5757     
5758           case Ist_Put: {
5759              Int b_offset
5760                 = MC_(get_otrack_shadow_offset)(
5761                      st->Ist.Put.offset,
5762                      sizeofIRType(typeOfIRExpr(mce->sb->tyenv, st->Ist.Put.data))
5763                   );
5764              if (b_offset >= 0) {
5765                 /* FIXME: this isn't an atom! */
5766                 stmt( 'B', mce, IRStmt_Put(b_offset + 2*mce->layout->total_sizeB, 
5767                                            schemeE( mce, st->Ist.Put.data )) );
5768              }
5769              break;
5770           }
5771     
5772           case Ist_WrTmp:
5773              assign( 'B', mce, findShadowTmpB(mce, st->Ist.WrTmp.tmp),
5774                                schemeE(mce, st->Ist.WrTmp.data) );
5775              break;
5776     
5777           case Ist_MBE:
5778           case Ist_NoOp:
5779           case Ist_Exit:
5780           case Ist_IMark:
5781              break;
5782     
5783           default:
5784              VG_(printf)("mc_translate.c: schemeS: unhandled: ");
5785              ppIRStmt(st); 
5786              VG_(tool_panic)("memcheck:schemeS");
5787        }
5788     }
5789     
5790     
5791     /*--------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5792     /*--- end                                           mc_translate.c ---*/
